docs {
  # Course Instances

  A CourseInstance represents a specific course offered to a batch in a
  particular semester. Because course_id and semester_id are owned by external
  services (Course Catalog & Academic Calendar), they are stored as logical UUID
  references — no foreign-key constraints exist for them in this service.

  ## Endpoints

  | Method | Path                                | Description                    |
  |--------|-------------------------------------|--------------------------------|
  | POST   | /api/v1/course-instances            | Create a new course instance   |
  | PUT    | /api/v1/course-instances/:id        | Update status of an instance   |
  | GET    | /api/v1/batches/:id/course-instances| List all instances for a batch |

  ## Status Lifecycle
  Planned → Active → Completed
                   → Cancelled

  ## Unique Constraint
  (course_id, semester_id, batch_id) — the same course cannot be scheduled
  for the same batch in the same semester more than once.

  ## Variable Automation
  - COURSE_INSTANCE_ID is saved automatically after a successful POST.
  - BATCH_ID must already be set (run Add Batch Member or Create Batch first).
}
